            <title><![CDATA[Unannounced Valve Game Listing Fuels Half-Life 3 Speculation]]></title>
            <link>https://insider-gaming.com/unannounced-valve-game-listing-fuels-half-life-3-speculation/</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/unannounced-valve-game-listing-fuels-half-life-3-speculation.1352461/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>
        
<p>The hype for a potential Half-Life 3 announcement continues to grow, especially with the knowledge that Valve has an unannounced game under its upcoming releases. The Half-Life 3 hope is higher than ever.</p>



<p>If we discount Half-Life: Alyx (admittedly a phenomenal VR experience), we’ve not had a mainline, multi-platform <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/half-life-player-count/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Half-Life</a> game since 2007. We know Valve and Gabe Newell have explained before that the company doesn’t feel the need to make a sequel, but it’s still one of gaming’s greatest mysteries.</p>







<p>Recent developments are pushing the narrative that Half-Life 3 could finally happen, and an unannounced Valve listing offers another glimmer of hope.</p>



<h2 id="h-valve-has-an-unannounced-upcoming-release">Valve Has An Unannounced Upcoming Release</h2>



<figure><figcaption>We’ll forgive you, Valve, it’s fine. Credit to Valve</figcaption></figure>



<p>If you go to Steam, search for any Valve game, then click on the company’s name, you’ll be taken to the main page. From here, a simple scroll down takes you to the company’s existing and upcoming portfolio.</p>



<p>Clicking on ‘Upcoming Releases’ reveals four products:</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="https://insider-gaming.com/deadlock-was-the-top-game-on-steam-in-august/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Deadlock</a>.</li>



<li>The new <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/steam-controller-2-announced-by-valve/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Steam Controller</a>.</li>



<li>The <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/valve-announces-the-steam-frame-vr-headset/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Steam Frame</a>.</li>



<li>The <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/valve-reveals-steam-machine/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Steam Machine</a>.</li>
</ul>



<p>All exciting Valve products and releases. However, if you look at the ‘All’ label in the left column, <strong>it clearly says 5, yet only 4 products are displayed</strong>. This more than likely <em>isn’t </em>an accident, and it suggests Valve has another product or game in the works, but perhaps something so big that Valve doesn’t want to announce it yet—see where we’re going with this?</p>



<figure><figcaption>Interesting. Credit to Steam</figcaption></figure>



<p>It wasn’t long ago that a <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/half-life-3-trailer-rumoured-to-be-in-production/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Half-Life 3 trailer was rumored to be in production</a>. If you don’t think this is enough evidence, how about the suggestion that <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/half-life-3-is-playable-end-to-end-its-claimed/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Half-Life 3 is ‘Playable End-to-End</a>‘?</p>



<p>Again, this is speculation, and we’re not saying this is Half-Life 3 confirmed (we wish). However, Alyx shows Valve isn’t afraid to make more Half-Life games, and with the wind very much in the company’s sails right now, it could be full Steam ahead on Half-Life 3.</p>







<p>We’ve had to sit on the Half-Life 2: Episode Two cliffhanger for nearly two decades, and we think it’s about time we finally get at least one final journey to wrap up the most incredible gaming saga.</p>



